WEBVTT

07:57.858 --> 08:01.823
I've always struggled with desiring acceptance from people, especially my peers.

08:02.324 --> 08:05.989
I went after things that were temporary and left me feeling pretty empty and broken.

08:06.289 --> 08:14.781
I was never religious growing up at all until college where tragedies were just like happening back to back.

08:15.482 --> 08:19.547
And I had an abortion with my first boyfriend.

08:19.928 --> 08:22.071
And in that same week, my dad went to prison.

08:22.111 --> 08:27.378
Through all of my young adult life, I was just riddled with pain.

08:27.490 --> 08:31.416
It came about from mainly just things I had experienced in life.

08:31.476 --> 08:33.659
Like I just, bad things happened to everybody.

08:33.759 --> 08:37.144
And I'm so susceptible to the questions of, am I loved?

08:37.205 --> 08:38.006
Am I admired?

08:38.266 --> 08:39.228
Is my art worthy?

08:39.488 --> 08:41.872
Or just as a human being, like did I do the right thing?

08:41.952 --> 08:42.653
Did I mess up?

08:42.753 --> 08:44.275
Did I hurt that person?

08:44.515 --> 08:46.979
I became incredibly self-righteous.

08:47.860 --> 08:51.606
I took immense pride and arrogance and the things that I did and didn't do.

08:52.067 --> 08:54.711
I felt fake and I felt like I was putting a facade for people.

08:55.111 --> 08:56.914
I was just completely filled with

08:57.058 --> 08:59.283
arrogance and selfishness.

08:59.564 --> 09:02.751
I decided I want to live for myself and do life on my own term.

09:02.931 --> 09:07.822
I was a drug addict, I was a thief, and I was a prisoner, both figuratively and literally.

09:08.203 --> 09:10.327
I experienced brokenness in my family.

09:10.748 --> 09:14.516
Depression when I lost my hair when I was diagnosed with alopecia ariata.

09:15.038 --> 09:17.042
I was almost aborted and

09:17.186 --> 09:22.953
My birth mother decided the operating room to change her mind and she decided to put it for adoption.

09:22.973 --> 09:30.083
October 30th, 2019, we lost our 21-year-old baby son, Andrew, in a tragic accident.

09:30.683 --> 09:36.951
And if I didn't have the hope that there was life and that death was not the end, I would not want to continue.

09:37.813 --> 09:42.098
But I do have the hope in Jesus that he came and he rescued us from death.

09:46.018 --> 09:49.243
So I turned to one of the two of the girls in the Acapella group.

09:49.263 --> 09:51.547
They were talking to me about this church they go to.

09:51.748 --> 09:53.090
And I was like, yeah, I'll give it a shot.

09:53.210 --> 09:54.272
I have nothing to lose.

09:54.292 --> 09:55.714
I just wept openly.

09:55.754 --> 09:57.437
I was an 18-year-old kid.

09:57.858 --> 10:01.624
I was living for, I think, sex drugs and rock and roll at the time.

10:02.045 --> 10:07.955
And one evening, a friend asked me a question of what Jesus meant by the unforgivable sin.

10:07.975 --> 10:09.618
I opened the Bible and started reading.

10:09.838 --> 10:12.242
And I found out that the way that I was living was sin.

10:12.322 --> 10:15.965
living in rebellion against God, living against him and just living for myself.

10:16.005 --> 10:19.249
So I read that man that the penalty of sin is death.

10:19.969 --> 10:23.973
And so I realized in that moment, man, this isn't good news for me, but then I've heard the good news.

10:24.313 --> 10:31.440
Jesus died and rose again to save me, to offer me a better new life.

10:32.241 --> 10:33.982
He rescued me for my self-righteousness.

10:34.023 --> 10:36.445
He showed me that I don't need to look to myself to be good.

10:36.965 --> 10:41.970
I can look to him because he lived a perfect life that I could not live and died the death

10:42.050 --> 10:43.753
for my sin that I should have died.

10:43.894 --> 10:51.589
But it was in that moment that Jesus came to me and said, son, all this time you've told yourself that you weren't good enough and I couldn't forgive you.

10:51.629 --> 10:54.976
I've already forgiven you and you need to forgive yourself.

10:55.377 --> 11:01.970
And he extends hope and forgiveness and that truth just washed over me completely.

11:05.922 --> 11:08.965
Jesus said, I have loved you with an everlasting love.

11:09.225 --> 11:10.587
That is the truest thing about me.

11:10.627 --> 11:17.213
And while we will disappoint each other in this life, there's only one that will never leave us, never forsake us and never disappoint us.

11:17.273 --> 11:19.856
He pursued me, he sought me out and he saved me.

11:19.876 --> 11:26.323
He continues to save me every single day because I need him just as much today as I did yesterday.

11:26.723 --> 11:30.126
Jesus truly transformed me through relationship with him.

11:30.567 --> 11:33.650
I don't know if I would be alive.

11:36.226 --> 11:45.861
Today if it wasn't for God and the people that he's brought into my life and the faith that I found.

11:46.242 --> 11:50.548
Whoever is your brother and sister in Christ, that is your true family.

11:50.669 --> 11:54.535
And so I'm now married and have my own daughter and have another baby on the way.

11:54.555 --> 11:59.282
I feel like Christ has given me such a freedom to tell me

11:59.490 --> 12:02.975
To my heart on such a personal level, child you are loved, you are accepted.

12:03.035 --> 12:07.241
Jesus is changing my life and my heart on a daily level.

12:07.301 --> 12:08.823
I feel like some days are such a struggle.

12:08.963 --> 12:21.541
And I still make mistakes all the time and I still fail all the time, but it doesn't matter because God has me and he's the one who's good, so I don't have to be, but I still try.

12:21.561 --> 12:24.946
He is with me in every circumstance.

12:24.994 --> 12:28.799
good and bad, and that is something I am eternally grateful for.

12:28.819 --> 12:45.161
I'm not saying it's easy to follow Jesus, but I do know that you'll never be alone, he'll never leave you, he'll never forsake you, and you can find peace and comfort in knowing that your identity is not found in anything in this world, but instead in the loving sacrifice that Jesus made for you and his death and resurrection on the cross.

12:45.381 --> 12:54.834
And now I know what it means to be fulfilled by the love of Christ, and I know what it feels like to be holy and completely covered in grace, love and mercy, and I'm never looking back.

12:54.914 --> 13:01.745
He has taken the ugly of our son's death and he's given me a beautiful hope that I will see my son again.

13:01.765 --> 13:10.398
And not only does he give me the hope of life to come, I have the hope that I can still live life even while I remain here until the day I see my son again.

13:10.739 --> 13:15.186
Jesus loves you and he loves you.

13:15.298 --> 13:17.142
deeply and unconditionally.

13:17.482 --> 13:21.350
Because of Jesus's work, I can say Jesus changed my life.

13:21.490 --> 13:22.793
Jesus changed my life.

13:22.833 --> 13:24.476
This is how Jesus changed my life.

13:24.516 --> 13:25.939
That's how Jesus changed my life.

13:25.979 --> 13:27.101
That's how Jesus changed my life.

13:27.121 --> 13:28.404
That's how Jesus changed my life.

13:28.424 --> 13:29.866
That's how Jesus changed my life.

13:30.087 --> 13:31.730
And that's how Jesus changed my life.

14:12.322 --> 14:12.756
There we go.

16:27.522 --> 16:28.163
Easter.

16:28.644 --> 16:36.361
My name is Jeremy Treat, I'm one of the pastors at Reality LA, and we are a church seeking the renewal of Los Angeles through the good news of Jesus.

16:37.163 --> 16:39.148
And right now it's a difficult time for our city.

16:39.528 --> 16:47.506
And yet in the midst of all of this, we believe that Jesus is alive and that he is bringing redemption and restoration and peace.

16:48.066 --> 16:51.331
And I especially want to welcome any visitors who are joining us today.

16:51.792 --> 16:57.521
Maybe this is a time where you're searching spiritually, or maybe someone just texted you a link to this and here you are.

16:58.121 --> 17:06.454
But either way, I hope that today that you're encouraged by the service and even more so that you hear about the hope that is available in Jesus.

17:07.155 --> 17:09.259
And to our church family, I miss you.

17:09.759 --> 17:11.162
I'm so grateful for you.

17:11.582 --> 17:14.066
And I'm glad to be able to celebrate with you today.

17:14.370 --> 17:22.784
Because in spite of all the changes that we're experiencing right now, we know that there's one thing that that's unchanging in his name is Jesus.

17:23.765 --> 17:27.672
And today, I'm preaching to you from the chapel in the Hope Center.

17:28.173 --> 17:37.769
This building was given to our church last year, and you all pitched in financially to help renovate this space, and it looks beautiful.

17:38.690 --> 17:41.074
And while this chapel may be empty now,

17:41.378 --> 17:47.984
I can just look out and imagine the generations of people who have sat in these pews over the last 90 years.

17:49.105 --> 17:56.172
And I know that right on the other side of the wall is where we've been feeding hundreds of meals every day to the most vulnerable in Hollywood.

17:57.713 --> 18:04.059
And I can look right at you and know that we are together in this, even if we're forced to be apart physically.

18:05.080 --> 18:11.026
And so with all the craziness going on in this world and in our lives, I want to call us to look to Christ.

18:11.458 --> 18:17.666
And to do so, I'm gonna read a passage from John chapter 20 verses 11 through 18.

18:17.706 --> 18:26.516
This is a story about a woman with a checkered past who had run out of hope, but then she had an encounter with Jesus and he changed her life.

18:27.277 --> 18:33.525
So I'll read from John chapter 20, starting in verse 11, and then I'll open our time in prayer.

18:35.387 --> 18:40.914
But Mary stood weeping outside the tomb, and as she wept, she stooped to look into the tomb.

18:41.410 --> 18:46.997
And she saw two angels in white sitting where the body of Jesus had laid, one at the head and one at the feet.

18:47.618 --> 18:49.800
They said to her, woman, why are you weeping?

18:50.561 --> 18:55.267
She said to them, they have taken away my Lord and I do not know where they have laid Him.

18:56.128 --> 19:02.036
Having said this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing, but she did not know that it was Jesus.

19:02.957 --> 19:05.580
Jesus said to her, woman, why are you weeping?

19:06.040 --> 19:07.282
Whom are you seeking?

19:07.842 --> 19:15.052
Supposing him to be the gardener, she said to him, sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away."

19:15.993 --> 19:17.496
Jesus said to her, Mary.

19:18.377 --> 19:21.882
She turned and said to him in Aramaic, Rabonai, which means teacher.

19:22.703 --> 19:33.458
Jesus said to her, do not cling to me, for I have not yet ascended to the Father, but go to my brothers and say to them, I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.

19:33.986 --> 19:40.693
Mary Magdalene went and announced to the disciples, I have seen the Lord and that he said, said these things to her.

19:40.733 --> 19:43.476
This is God's word, let's pray together.

19:45.758 --> 19:56.489
God, we come before you in this time lamenting the loss and the pain and the physical illness in our city and all over this world.

19:56.669 --> 20:01.074
Lord, we cry out in grief in such a difficult time.

20:01.218 --> 20:09.951
And yet, Lord, as we lament, we also celebrate believing and declaring that Christ is risen.

20:09.991 --> 20:14.758
And so, Lord, we pray today that you would change our lives.

20:15.559 --> 20:25.554
We ask that where there is anxiety that you would give peace, where there is fear that you would replace it with faith, and where there is despair that you would give us hope.

20:26.595 --> 20:31.122
Lord, I pray for every single person watching this or listening to this right now,

20:31.298 --> 20:34.102
that you administer to them exactly where they're at.

20:34.964 --> 20:40.492
Lord, I thank you that you know them, you know their story, you know their heart, and you love them.

20:41.173 --> 20:46.161
Lord, would you speak to them in this time and bring change in their lives?

20:46.261 --> 20:50.728
God, we need your grace, we need your mercy to transform us.

20:51.750 --> 20:59.762
And Lord, we pray that not only for ourselves, we pray for all of the churches across the city of Los Angeles today who have online services going on.

20:59.970 --> 21:01.031
Lord, would you bless them?

21:01.051 --> 21:04.675
Would you do a mighty work in this city as the gospel goes forth?

21:05.116 --> 21:08.119
Would you give people hope and peace in Christ?

21:08.640 --> 21:10.281
We pray this in His name.

21:11.082 --> 21:11.423
Amen.

21:12.184 --> 21:12.484
Amen.

21:15.127 --> 21:18.891
Well, 2020 is not quite the year that we expected it to be, is it?

21:19.892 --> 21:23.156
Remember back in January, New Year, New Me?

21:23.176 --> 21:25.298
New decade, New Me.

21:25.890 --> 21:31.799
But then we quickly realized that it's an election year and all started freaking out about politics.

21:32.700 --> 21:47.743
But just as the heat was being turned up in politics, we received the devastating news of a helicopter crash right here in our city with Kobe Bryant and his 13 year old daughter and seven other beloved people who died that day.

21:48.564 --> 21:52.690
And our city was reeling and as we're grieving that,

21:53.282 --> 21:57.287
There's another headline about a virus that's quickly spreading.

21:58.068 --> 22:02.313
Of course, that headline has turned into a global pandemic.

22:03.014 --> 22:12.705
And today, over 1.5 million cases of the coronavirus have swept the globe and close to 100,000 people have died.

22:13.546 --> 22:20.274
There are countless people grieving those who have passed and many who are living in fear of what could come.

22:21.026 --> 22:26.753
And with cities essentially shutting down, the physical illness has then led to financial hardship.

22:27.555 --> 22:33.022
Many of you have lost work or have lost your job and you don't know how you're going to pay your bills.

22:34.604 --> 22:38.669
And all of these hardships have caused people to ask the deeper questions of life.

22:39.310 --> 22:40.371
Where is God in this?

22:40.932 --> 22:41.813
Is there any hope?

22:42.434 --> 22:44.136
What really matters in life?

22:45.057 --> 22:45.618
In fact,

22:45.922 --> 22:54.775
People are searching so much there have been more Google searches for the word prayer in the last month than there ever have been in the history of Google.

22:55.756 --> 22:58.320
But of course you don't need the internet to tell you that.

22:59.321 --> 23:07.253
I know that this pandemic has disrupted your life and brought anxiety and loss and fear for so many of us.

23:08.194 --> 23:09.957
And so everyone's looking for answers.

23:10.638 --> 23:11.559
Where can we turn?

23:11.619 --> 23:13.522
What can be done?

23:13.698 --> 23:15.821
Who can bring change in my life?

23:17.364 --> 23:20.249
And so today, I want you to hear this.

23:21.010 --> 23:22.933
Jesus can change your life.

23:24.135 --> 23:32.489
And I want to walk through this story in John chapter 20 so that we can see who Jesus is, what he accomplished, and what it can mean for us.

23:33.390 --> 23:38.098
And let me give you just a little bit of the context leading up to John chapter 20.

23:38.594 --> 23:39.856
Jesus came.

23:39.896 --> 23:45.587
He entered into a world marred by sin in order to bring healing and hope.

23:46.368 --> 23:52.119
But while he lived a life of love and peace, he was crucified and then placed in a tomb.

23:52.940 --> 23:58.410
And so when you come to John chapter 20, there's a woman named Mary Magdalene who goes to the tomb.

23:59.392 --> 24:02.898
Now Mary is a woman who what we know about her basically is that

24:03.042 --> 24:10.653
She was tormented by demons and therefore she would have suffered much physically, emotionally and spiritually.

24:11.354 --> 24:16.282
But then she met Jesus and he set her free from this bondage and he gave her a new life.

24:17.283 --> 24:24.734
And so when Mary sees that the tomb is empty, she then runs and gets the other disciples, she goes to them and says, you've got to see this.

24:24.794 --> 24:30.162
And so they run to the tomb and they're all there and they look in the tomb, they're astonished that it's empty.

24:30.946 --> 24:34.991
But then when the other disciples leave, Mary sticks around.

24:35.912 --> 24:38.856
And look what happens in verse 11.

24:38.876 --> 24:42.981
It says, but Mary stood weeping outside the tomb.

24:43.021 --> 24:46.745
And as she wept, she stooped to look into the tomb.

24:47.546 --> 24:49.669
And here's what I want you to notice at the beginning of this story.

24:49.729 --> 24:50.770
What is Mary doing?

24:51.371 --> 24:53.754
She's weeping and she's looking.

24:55.636 --> 25:00.722
See, she had assumed that the guards or somebody had taken the body of Jesus elsewhere

25:01.314 --> 25:05.721
And so she was crushed, overwhelmed with grief and searching for hope.

25:06.983 --> 25:10.328
Now there's a lot about Mary that I think we can identify with today.

25:11.330 --> 25:14.655
Many people in our city are weeping and looking.

25:15.736 --> 25:20.504
We're weeping because there's been a lot of loss and we need to express our grief.

25:21.245 --> 25:24.069
We're looking, trying to figure out how to move forward.

25:25.612 --> 25:29.618
But then Mary looks in the tomb and sees two angels in there.

25:29.858 --> 25:32.702
sitting in the very place where the body of Jesus was laying.

25:33.463 --> 25:36.066
And the angels ask her, why are you weeping?

25:36.927 --> 25:38.929
She tells them because they've taken away my Lord.

25:39.871 --> 25:41.092
But then look at verse 14.

25:42.274 --> 25:50.524
It says, having said this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing, but she did not know that it was Jesus.

25:51.485 --> 25:52.947
Can you imagine this scene?

25:52.987 --> 25:54.349
Here's Mary.

25:54.629 --> 25:55.951
She's looking for Jesus.

25:56.171 --> 25:56.952
She's weeping.

25:57.193 --> 25:58.354
Where could he be?

25:58.530 --> 26:00.292
Where's the body she's looking for?

26:00.612 --> 26:02.154
And he's right in front of her.

26:02.194 --> 26:05.538
And she doesn't recognize that it's him.

26:05.558 --> 26:15.849
Now, we might hear that and have a hard time understanding why Mary could not recognize Jesus, but how often do we do the same thing?

26:17.330 --> 26:18.972
We're weeping and we're looking.

26:20.013 --> 26:21.575
Maybe we're even frustrated.

26:21.655 --> 26:22.576
Where is God?

26:22.596 --> 26:24.818
And yet he's pursuing you.

26:25.539 --> 26:26.420
He's loving you.

26:26.920 --> 26:28.402
He's caring for you.

26:29.186 --> 26:32.031
And how often do you not recognize that he's right there with you?

26:33.433 --> 26:39.503
It goes on in verse 15, and Jesus then speaks to her asking, why are you weeping?

26:40.124 --> 26:41.587
Whom are you seeking?

26:42.668 --> 26:46.595
Now, I want you to notice the way that Jesus approaches this woman who is hurting.

26:47.637 --> 26:48.779
He initiates with her.

26:49.660 --> 26:51.062
He acknowledges her pain.

26:51.924 --> 26:55.730
He comes to her not with words of accusation, but with words of grace.

26:56.642 --> 26:59.286
But she still doesn't recognize him.

26:59.566 --> 27:01.989
In fact, she thinks that he's the gardener.

27:02.049 --> 27:06.535
She's like, hey, listen, if you know where the body is, then let me know so I can find it.

27:06.555 --> 27:08.077
But otherwise, leave me alone.

27:08.117 --> 27:10.501
Like go back to picking weeds or something, buddy.

27:10.541 --> 27:12.483
Like I'm looking for Jesus.

27:12.884 --> 27:14.867
And she's talking to Jesus.

27:14.927 --> 27:16.529
It's almost unthinkable.

27:18.872 --> 27:21.415
But then the turning point of the story comes in verse 16.

27:23.518 --> 27:26.322
It says, Jesus said to her, Mary.

27:27.586 --> 27:31.731
And as soon as he calls her name, she recognizes him.

27:33.032 --> 27:37.377
Now I want you to remember that Jesus didn't appear at this moment.

27:37.417 --> 27:38.158
He had been there.

27:38.578 --> 27:42.382
Remember pursuing her, speaking to her, acknowledging her pain and grief.

27:42.683 --> 27:44.004
He didn't just appear then.

27:44.044 --> 27:49.090
She just didn't recognize him until he called her by her name.

27:50.231 --> 27:52.654
And here's what I want you to hear today.

27:53.935 --> 27:54.816
I know that you're her name.

27:55.557 --> 27:56.338
You're searching.

27:57.026 --> 27:58.948
But Jesus knows your name.

27:59.929 --> 28:02.452
He knows your story, your struggles.

28:03.213 --> 28:04.274
He knows your fears.

28:04.754 --> 28:06.096
He knows your insecurities.

28:06.776 --> 28:07.657
And He loves you.

28:09.219 --> 28:14.204
And not just the future you, not just the good you, not just the spiritual you.

28:14.484 --> 28:15.846
He loves you.

28:15.886 --> 28:21.432
He loves the failing you, the struggling you, the sinful you.

28:21.492 --> 28:23.474
He loves you.

28:24.098 --> 28:30.385
And not only does he love you, he knows you and he calls you by name.

28:30.425 --> 28:36.151
Now think about this, with Mary, she was looking for Jesus.

28:37.353 --> 28:41.777
But we know from our perspective that it was Jesus who came and found her.

28:42.618 --> 28:43.980
And that's the way that it works.

28:44.801 --> 28:50.427
Our pursuit of God leads to us realizing that he's been pursuing us all along.

28:50.447 --> 28:53.170
And so listen, in your life,

28:53.602 --> 28:54.183
He's there.

28:54.243 --> 28:55.965
Do you see Him?

28:56.966 --> 28:57.826
Do you hear Him?

28:58.387 --> 29:00.509
Do you sense His love for you?

29:01.871 --> 29:03.693
Here's what I want you to notice about this story.

29:04.594 --> 29:07.417
It starts with Mary weeping and looking.

29:08.238 --> 29:13.463
But then in verse 18, it ends with her rejoicing and proclaiming.

29:14.644 --> 29:20.050
See, she had had an encounter with the resurrected Christ and it changed her life.

29:20.450 --> 29:27.240
And that's my prayer for you today, that you would be able to say, Jesus changed my life.

29:28.802 --> 29:37.054
But the way to experience that change is not just through hearing a story about Jesus, but by believing in the good news of Jesus, the gospel.

29:38.015 --> 29:46.027
And the gospel is that even while we're sinners, Christ died for our sins and rose from the dead to make us new.

29:46.047 --> 29:48.050
And so let me ask you this.

29:48.802 --> 29:51.245
Are you willing to acknowledge your sin?

29:51.285 --> 29:58.752
Are you willing to acknowledge that you've rejected God, you've run from Him, and you've chosen your own way?

29:58.792 --> 30:05.459
Do you believe scripture when it says we have all sinned and fallen short of the glory of God?

30:06.901 --> 30:09.344
And yet, God doesn't give up on us.

30:10.284 --> 30:11.946
God doesn't give up on you.

30:11.986 --> 30:15.570
He pursues you with love and mercy.

30:16.194 --> 30:20.959
Jesus came and he lived a perfect life and then he died a sacrificial death.

30:22.261 --> 30:26.025
So when people say, where is God in all of this suffering?

30:26.345 --> 30:28.488
Well, the answer is he's with us.

30:29.529 --> 30:33.553
He's the God of the cross who enters into our suffering and our brokenness.

30:35.516 --> 30:39.600
But when Jesus went to the cross, he wasn't just entering into our pain.

30:40.061 --> 30:41.402
He was dying for our sin.

30:41.462 --> 30:44.946
He took our place on the cross.

30:45.346 --> 30:48.209
so that we could experience His grace and peace.

30:49.311 --> 30:52.234
He was rejected so that we could be accepted.

30:52.254 --> 30:56.620
He bore judgment so that we could be declared righteous.

30:57.581 --> 31:00.985
He took our shame so that we could be cleansed.

31:02.206 --> 31:04.049
But of course, He didn't stay on the cross.

31:05.050 --> 31:07.473
And when they put Him in the tomb, He didn't stay there either.

31:08.294 --> 31:09.615
No, He has risen.

31:09.655 --> 31:11.758
The tomb is empty.

31:11.798 --> 31:15.122
He conquered sin, Satan, and death.

31:15.202 --> 31:19.068
And he walked out of that tomb 2,000 years ago with power.

31:19.108 --> 31:21.791
Power to set us free from our past.

31:22.412 --> 31:24.375
Power to give us hope for the future.

31:24.435 --> 31:27.399
Power to live with purpose today.

31:28.160 --> 31:29.803
Jesus is alive.

31:30.384 --> 31:34.530
And this isn't just some religious sentiment that won't affect your real life.

31:35.371 --> 31:40.498
Because Jesus is alive, you don't have to live for the approval of others anymore.

31:40.802 --> 31:43.665
You don't have to be defined by your failures any longer.

31:43.706 --> 31:47.130
You don't have to be crushed under the weight of your guilt.

31:47.150 --> 31:49.312
You don't have to live in fear anymore.

31:49.412 --> 31:49.773
Why?

31:50.153 --> 31:52.216
Because Jesus is alive.

31:52.716 --> 31:54.879
Come on, you can say amen to your screen.

31:55.139 --> 31:57.622
You can say hallelujah so your neighbor can hear it.

31:57.863 --> 31:59.024
This is good news.

31:59.305 --> 32:00.146
This is truth.

32:00.446 --> 32:02.528
This is God's word for you.

32:02.589 --> 32:06.954
And all of this is incredible.

32:07.855 --> 32:08.756
It's remarkable.

32:09.597 --> 32:10.418
But here's the thing.

32:11.202 --> 32:15.208
It cannot be earned, but only received.

32:15.869 --> 32:16.429
It's grace.

32:17.431 --> 32:18.272
It's a gift.

32:19.634 --> 32:22.918
But you might say, listen, Pastor, you don't know what I've done.

32:22.958 --> 32:24.881
I've gone too far.

32:25.923 --> 32:30.409
But what I would say to you is that God's grace goes further than your sin.

32:30.469 --> 32:34.735
God's redemption is greater than your rebellion.

32:35.897 --> 32:36.978
And this grace

32:37.186 --> 32:38.588
is so powerful.

32:38.908 --> 32:44.436
This grace is so life-changing that you might even call it amazing grace.

32:45.497 --> 32:48.761
Now, I know that you've heard the hymn, amazing grace.

32:49.602 --> 32:57.072
When you hear that, you might think of religious people who've got it all together, that they act a certain way and they don't struggle with sin.

32:57.092 --> 32:57.873
They're not tempted.

32:58.254 --> 33:01.298
When you hear that hymn, you probably think whoever wrote that hymn

33:01.410 --> 33:03.112
They're like a spiritual all-star.

33:03.132 --> 33:04.073
They never struggle.

33:04.273 --> 33:05.415
They're always at church.

33:05.435 --> 33:07.037
They've got the whole Bible memorized.

33:07.377 --> 33:09.079
They've been perfect their whole lives.

33:09.960 --> 33:11.782
But that couldn't be further from the truth.

33:12.583 --> 33:15.587
The hymn Amazing Grace was written by a man named John Newton.

33:16.067 --> 33:18.610
He lived in the 18th century in England.

33:19.451 --> 33:25.298
And not only was John Newton an ungodly man, he was actually the captain of a slave ship.

33:25.954 --> 33:31.523
He was overseeing, transporting and trading human beings as property.

33:32.324 --> 33:37.452
It's hard to imagine anything more evil, any more rebellion against God.

33:38.995 --> 33:48.770
And yet one day he was on the ship in a storm and he was confronted with his own sin and he saw God's grace and he trusted in Christ.

33:49.311 --> 33:51.314
Jesus changed his life.

33:52.098 --> 34:03.453
And not only was he satisfied in God and did he have a relationship with God, but he went literally from overseeing the selling of slaves to devoting his life to the abolition of slavery.

34:07.699 --> 34:08.701
And how could this happen?

34:08.761 --> 34:10.703
How could such a radical change happen?

34:10.743 --> 34:16.131
A man who's running against God, who's making others suffer so much?

34:16.151 --> 34:19.715
How could he change from that to living for God and setting others free?

34:20.497 --> 34:21.618
It's only by grace.

34:22.050 --> 34:22.991
Amazing grace.

34:24.753 --> 34:28.658
And so reflecting on his own story, John Newton penned these words.

34:29.219 --> 34:30.240
Amazing grace.

34:30.700 --> 34:34.145
How sweet the sound that saved a wretch like me.

34:34.986 --> 34:40.292
I once was lost, but now I'm found, was blind, but now I see.

34:41.654 --> 34:43.196
Newton's life was changed.

34:43.816 --> 34:48.482
And even went on to become a pastor and to write other hymns that are still sung today.

34:49.523 --> 34:51.826
But while there was much growth in his life,

34:52.098 --> 34:54.662
he never outgrew his need for grace.

34:55.624 --> 35:05.239
And at the end of his life, after all that he'd been through, he said this, although my memory is fading, I remember two things very clearly.

35:06.060 --> 35:09.525
I am a great sinner, and Christ is a great savior.

35:11.588 --> 35:20.242
Now I want you to know that the grace of God is not just in the Bible for Mary, and it's not just in history for John Newton,

35:20.706 --> 35:25.256
I want you to know that Jesus is alive and he's changing lives today.

35:26.419 --> 35:37.042
This week we've done something in our church where we had people share their stories on social media about how Jesus changed their life and just put the hashtag, Jesus changed my life.

35:37.506 --> 35:42.533
And many people in our church have done this, other churches across the nation and even the globe have joined in.

35:42.793 --> 35:45.356
There's literally thousands of stories.

35:45.437 --> 35:57.893
If you don't believe what the Bible says about the resurrection of Jesus, I would encourage you just to go and click on the hashtag and listen to story after story after story about how Jesus is changing lives all over the world.

35:58.634 --> 36:04.562
And as I listened to these stories this past week, I was reminded of the power of God's grace.

36:05.314 --> 36:14.983
I heard stories of people who grew up Hindu or Buddhist or Muslim or who grew up atheist or who grew up in a cult and yet Jesus changed their life.

36:16.004 --> 36:24.512
I heard stories of people who grew up in the church or who grew up hating the church or were wounded by the church, but Jesus changed their life.

36:25.353 --> 36:31.979
I heard stories of people who were in prison and prostitution and addiction, but Jesus changed their life.

36:32.880 --> 36:34.962
I heard stories of people who were depressed

36:35.138 --> 36:40.003
who are anxious, who are scared, who are confused, but Jesus changed their life.

36:40.904 --> 36:53.015
I heard people telling their stories in Spanish, in Romanian, in French, in Portuguese, and other languages, and I didn't understand everything they said, but I'm pretty sure it was that Jesus changed their life because that was the hashtag.

36:54.176 --> 37:04.466
I heard stories of people who have done terrible things, and I heard stories of people who have had terrible things done to them, and yet Jesus changed their life.

37:05.666 --> 37:09.531
And if he changed them, then he can change you.

37:12.394 --> 37:15.418
Now I've tried to lay out the gospel as clearly as possible.

37:17.160 --> 37:18.963
But the last thing I wanna talk about is this.

37:19.964 --> 37:23.448
The way that we receive God's grace is through faith.

37:24.349 --> 37:27.994
By trusting him and entrusting our lives to him.

37:28.995 --> 37:34.482
In Ephesians chapter two, verse eight, it says that we are saved by grace

37:34.690 --> 37:35.931
through faith.

37:36.812 --> 37:38.594
So salvation is by grace.

37:39.455 --> 37:47.422
That means that your relationship with God does not depend on what you do for Him, but on what He has done for you in Christ.

37:48.043 --> 37:50.945
Salvation is a gift to be given.

37:51.005 --> 37:55.490
Radical, utter, sheer grace.

37:56.531 --> 37:58.312
But a gift has to be received.

37:59.253 --> 38:04.338
If somebody tossed you a present, you would open your hands to receive it.

38:05.090 --> 38:11.280
And so faith is an opening of our hands to receive of God's grace.

38:12.742 --> 38:14.144
God is gracious to you.

38:14.885 --> 38:17.690
The question is, will you resist it or will you receive it?

38:19.372 --> 38:28.006
But the problem is, what we have to acknowledge is that our natural proclivity in our sin is to have our fist closed tight.

38:29.268 --> 38:31.992
We want to have a tight grip on our own lives.

38:32.072 --> 38:33.234
We want control.

38:33.634 --> 38:34.936
I want to do things my way.

38:34.956 --> 38:36.398
I want to do things from my glory.

38:36.779 --> 38:37.760
I want to get the credit.

38:38.041 --> 38:44.330
And so we have tight fists, but faith is giving up of control to the Lord.

38:45.592 --> 38:48.416
Faith is saying, God, I want you to lead my life.

38:49.818 --> 38:52.482
Faith is saying, Jesus, my life belongs to you.

38:52.583 --> 39:02.898
And we end up in a posture of surrender before the Lord, a posture of faith and receiving saying, God, my life belongs to you.

39:04.130 --> 39:23.908
And it's then that God's grace floods our hearts, that He changes us from the inside out, that He gives us a new heart, that He gives us a new identity, that He gives us a new purpose, that He gives us a new family, so that we can live for Him in every aspect of our lives.

39:24.730 --> 39:26.994
So trust in Christ today.

39:27.554 --> 39:33.021
For those of you who are not Christians and you're hearing this news and you're saying, this is different than what I thought Christianity was.

39:33.041 --> 39:40.251
And I didn't know this good news of God's grace in Christ, trust in Christ today for salvation and become a Christian.

39:40.831 --> 39:42.313
Give everything in your life to Jesus.

39:42.874 --> 39:55.090
For those of you who are followers of Jesus, remember that he has risen and that the same power that rose Jesus from the grave dwells in us by faith live by the power of Christ.

39:56.930 --> 39:59.333
Now listen, this world is hurting.

40:00.394 --> 40:06.061
Our city is reeling, but friends, the tomb is empty.

40:07.262 --> 40:16.092
And so by God's grace, we can say today and every day, no matter what comes, Jesus changed my life.

40:16.112 --> 40:16.833
Let's pray together.

40:19.356 --> 40:24.562
God, we thank you for the abundance of your grace that you have given us in Christ.

40:25.634 --> 40:27.076
And Lord, we confess our sin.

40:27.136 --> 40:28.978
We confess that we have run from you.

40:29.038 --> 40:30.580
We have chosen our own way.

40:30.620 --> 40:47.282
And we thank you that even when we run from you and when we rebel against you, that you pursue us in your love, we thank you that while we were enemies, that you have made us sons and daughters and brought us into your kingdom and given us a place at your table.

40:48.763 --> 40:53.970
God, I pray for anyone right now who doesn't know you as Lord and Savior.

40:54.786 --> 41:04.400
that you would give them the faith to trust in you, to confess their sin and simply say, Lord, I've sinned against you.

41:05.362 --> 41:11.851
I believe that you died from my sins and that you rose from the grave so that I can have abundant and eternal life.

41:13.213 --> 41:14.856
I receive you as my Lord and Savior.

41:14.876 --> 41:18.341
I trust you with everything in my life and I will follow you all of my days.

41:19.783 --> 41:22.527
God, give us faith to trust in you.

41:23.729 --> 41:24.530
Lord, I pray,

41:25.282 --> 41:31.631
that you would teach us to love one another, even in a time where it feels so isolating.

41:32.712 --> 41:39.621
Teach us to support one another and to serve one another and to be creative in the ways that we build one another up.

41:41.083 --> 41:50.036
And God, we pray moving forward that you would use us for your purposes and your glory in this city, in a city that's broken and hurting.

41:50.757 --> 41:54.001
We pray that your renewal would spread throughout the city God.

41:54.021 --> 41:54.802
We love you.

41:55.362 --> 41:58.727
We thank you that Christ has risen and that we can have hope in Him.

41:59.128 --> 42:25.106
We pray this in His name, amen.

42:27.010 --> 42:47.250
The burning sun was dead The savior of the world was falling His body on the cross His blood poured out for us The weight of every cross alone

